OL,5, A group of trick-or-treaters who bought
OL,6, gifts for a great-grandmother are being
OL,7, sought by the woman's family to say    
OL,8, thank you.                             
OL,10,FBrenda Burdon, 86, was visited at home 
OL,11,Fin Denton, Newcastle, by three children
OL,12,Fcalled Jessie, Olivia and Walter.      
OL,14,FShe apologised for having no treats to 
OL,15,Fgive them when they visited on Thursday
OL,16,Fbut the next day they returned with a  
OL,17,Fcard, chocolates and a #10 note.       
OL,19,FMs Burdon's family said they had been  
OL,20,Famazed by the children's actions.      
